item.title: For the record, this is why we split up with England
item.dc:creator: Soup
item.description:
Haze:

Typical of us Brits. It could have been something exciting, like traffic injuries, or sword-fights with pirates, or disputing the subtotal at a supermarket with a Transformer sales-rep (Preferable Ultra Magnus , he was badass), but no, it had to be fucking biscuits.

I prefer something like this to common-as-much traffic injuries or construction site injuries. We’re fucking original.

“What’s that, you hurt your head with a breeze block? I hurt mine with a fucking biscuit, bitch.”

item.title: For the record, this is why we split up with England
item.dc:creator: Mangled
item.description:
That article just isn’t true. The word ‘injury’ is used so dubiously… personally I don’t consider losing a tooth when eating an injury… and I’m sure almost all children in Britain have lost a tooth from eating a biscuit. Neither do I consider ‘choking’ on crumbs to be an injury.

So here’s the statistics which I found on another version of the article…

An estimated 25 million adults have been injured while eating during a tea or coffee break - with at least 500 landing themselves in hospital, the survey revealed.

No mention of biscuits or cookies.
